methods.brief: Reset the vector (as if were just created an empty vector). This leaves arrays!

methods.name: empty
methods.brief: Reset the vector (as if were just created an empty vector)

methods.name: reallyClear
methods.brief: Clear even if in a bad way.

methods.name: operator=
methods.brief: Assignment operator.

methods.name: operator=
methods.brief: Assignment operator from a CoinPackedVectorBase.

methods.name: copy
methods.brief: Copy the contents of one vector into another.
methods.detailed: If multiplier is 1 It is the equivalent of = but if vectors are same size does not re-allocate memory just clears and copies

methods.name: borrowVector
methods.brief: Borrow ownership of the arguments to this vector.
methods.detailed: Size is the length of the unpacked elements vector.

methods.name: returnVector
methods.brief: Return ownership of the arguments to this vector.

methods.name: setVector
methods.brief: Set vector numberIndices, indices, and elements.
methods.detailed: NumberIndices is the length of both the indices and elements vectors. The indices and elements vectors are copied into this class instance's member data. Assumed to have no duplicates

methods.name: setVector
methods.brief: Set vector size, indices, and elements.
methods.detailed: Size is the length of the unpacked elements vector. The indices and elements vectors are copied into this class instance's member data. We do not check for duplicate indices

methods.name: setConstant
methods.brief: Elements set to have the same scalar value.

methods.name: setFull
methods.brief: Indices are not specified and are taken to be 0,1,...,size-1.

methods.name: setElement
methods.brief: Set an existing element in the indexed vector The first argument is the "index" into the elements() array.

methods.name: insert
methods.brief: Insert an element into the vector.

methods.name: quickInsert
methods.brief: Insert a nonzero element into the vector.

methods.name: add
methods.brief: Insert or if exists add an element into the vector Any resulting zero elements will be made tiny.

methods.name: quickAdd
methods.brief: Insert or if exists add an element into the vector Any resulting zero elements will be made tiny.

methods.name: quickAddNonZero
methods.brief: Insert or if exists add an element into the vector Any resulting zero elements will be made tiny.
methods.detailed: This knows element is nonzero This version does no checking

methods.name: zero
methods.brief: Makes nonzero tiny.

methods.name: clean
methods.brief: set all small values to zero and return number remaining

methods.name: cleanAndPack
methods.brief: Same but packs down.

methods.name: cleanAndPackSafe
methods.brief: Same but packs down and is safe (i.e. if order is odd)

methods.name: setPacked
methods.brief: Mark as packed.

methods.name: checkClear
methods.brief: For debug check vector is clear i.e. no elements.

methods.name: checkClean
methods.brief: For debug check vector is clean i.e. elements match indices.
